MapObjects

Class Interactable

  • java.lang.Object
    • MapObjects.Interactable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Animal, Litter, Plant, Player, Receptacle, River

    public class Interactable
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Highest class in the Game object Heirarchy. Contains basic attributes for location and dimensions, as well as collision detection.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Method Detail

      • getCollisionRect

        public java.awt.Rectangle getCollisionRect()
        Returns a rectangle representing the collision box of the Interactable, relative to world coordinate 0,0. Note that this is different from the relativeCollisionBox used internally.
        Returns:
        The collision box of this Interactable relative to world coordinate 0,0.

      • setRelativeCollisionRect

        protected void setRelativeCollisionRect(int dx,
                                        int dy,
                                        int width,
                                        int height)
        Sets the relative collision box of this interactable. Should only be called by subclasses. Note that these coordinates are relative to the 0,0 position of the Interactable at any given time.
        Parameters:
        dx - The x-coordinate of the left side of the box, relative to the Interactable's x-position.
        dy - The y-coordinate of the top side of the box, relative to the Interactable's y-position.
        width - The width of the box
        height - The height of the box

        Determines whether this Interactable and another are colliding according to their collision boxes.
        Returns:
        True if the two interactables are colliding; false otherwise.

      • addXLocation

        public void addXLocation(int dx)
        Adds to the x-coordinate of the Interactable. For example, if a can is at x=200 and someone calls can.addXLocation(50), then the can will now be located at x=250.
        Parameters:
        dx - The amount to add to the x-coordinate

      • addYLocation

        public void addYLocation(int dy)
        Adds to the y-coordinate of the Interactable. For example, if a can is at y=200 and someone calls can.addYLocation(50), then the can will now be located at y=250.
        Parameters:
        dy - The amount to add to the y-coordinate
